SetUseFrames

public void SetUseFrames(boolean inUseFrames)
Enables experimental Push "frames" When frames are enabled, each Push subtree is given a fresh set of stacks (a "frame") when it executes. When a frame is pushed, the top value from each stack is passed to the new frame, and likewise when the frame pops, allowing for input arguments and return values.
